  "content": [
    {
      "type": "book",
      "marker": "id",
      "content": ["- Berean Study Bible"],
      "code": "PHM"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "h",
      "content": ["Philemon\n"]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "toc1",
      "content": ["Philemon\n"]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "mt1",
      "content": ["Philemon\n"]
    },
    {
      "type": "chapter",
      "marker": "c",
      "number": "1",
      "sid": "PHM 1"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "s1",
      "content": ["Greetings from Paul and Timothy\n"]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "r",
      "content": ["(Philippians 1:1–2; Colossians 1:1–2)\n"]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "b"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "m",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "1",
          "sid": "PHM 1:1"
        },
        "Paul, a prisoner of Christ Jesus, and Timothy our brother, \n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "b"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "m",
      "content": [
        "To Philemon our beloved fellow worker, \n",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "2",
          "sid": "PHM 1:2"
        },
        "to Apphia our sister, to Archippus our fellow soldier, and to the church that meets at your ",
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "f",
          "content": [
            " ",
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": ["1:2 "]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": [
                "You and Your are singular throughout this letter, except in verses 3, 22, and 25."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "caller": "+"
        },
        " house: \n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "b"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "m",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "3",
          "sid": "PHM 1:3"
        },
        "Grace and peace to you from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ. \n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "s1",
      "content": ["Philemon’s Faith and Love\n"]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "b"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "m",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "4",
          "sid": "PHM 1:4"
        },
        "I always thank my God, remembering you in my prayers, \n",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "5",
          "sid": "PHM 1:5"
        },
        "because I hear about your faith in the Lord Jesus and your love for all the saints. \n",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "6",
          "sid": "PHM 1:6"
        },
        "I pray that your partnership in the faith may become effective as you fully acknowledge every good thing that is ours in Christ. \n",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "7",
          "sid": "PHM 1:7"
        },
        "I take great joy and encouragement in your love, because you, brother, have refreshed the hearts of the saints. \n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "s1",
      "content": ["Paul’s Appeal for Onesimus\n"]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "b"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "m",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "8",
          "sid": "PHM 1:8"
        },
        "So although in Christ I am bold enough to order you to do what is proper, \n",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "9",
          "sid": "PHM 1:9"
        },
        "I prefer to appeal on the basis of love. For I, Paul, am now aged, and a prisoner of Christ Jesus as well. \n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "b"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "m",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "10",
          "sid": "PHM 1:10"
        },
        "I appeal to you for my child Onesimus,",
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "f",
          "content": [
            " ",
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": ["1:10 "]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": [
                "Onesimus means useful (see verse 11) or beneficial (see verse 20)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "caller": "+"
        },
        " whose father I became while I was in chains. \n",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "11",
          "sid": "PHM 1:11"
        },
        "Formerly he was useless to you, but now he has become useful both to you and to me. \n",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "12",
          "sid": "PHM 1:12"
        },
        "I am sending back to you him who is my very heart. \n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "b"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "m",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "13",
          "sid": "PHM 1:13"
        },
        "I would have liked to keep him with me, so that on your behalf he could minister to me in my chains for the gospel. \n",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "14",
          "sid": "PHM 1:14"
        },
        "But I did not want to do anything without your consent, so that your goodness will not be out of compulsion, but by your own free will. \n",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "15",
          "sid": "PHM 1:15"
        },
        "For perhaps this is why he was separated from you for a while, so that you might have him back for good—\n",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "16",
          "sid": "PHM 1:16"
        },
        "no longer as a slave, but better than a slave, as a beloved brother. He is especially beloved to me, but even more so to you, both in person and in the Lord. \n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "b"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "m",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "17",
          "sid": "PHM 1:17"
        },
        "So if you consider me a partner, receive him as you would receive me. \n",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "18",
          "sid": "PHM 1:18"
        },
        "But if he has wronged you in any way or owes you anything, charge it to my account. \n",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "19",
          "sid": "PHM 1:19"
        },
        "I, Paul, write this with my own hand. I will repay it—not to mention that you owe me your very self. \n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "b"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "m",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "20",
          "sid": "PHM 1:20"
        },
        "Yes, brother, let me have some benefit ",
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "f",
          "content": [
            " ",
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": ["1:20 "]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": ["Greek onaimēn, a play on the name Onesimus"]
            }
          ],
          "caller": "+"
        },
        " from you in the Lord. Refresh my heart in Christ. \n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "b"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "m",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "21",
          "sid": "PHM 1:21"
        },
        "Confident of your obedience, I write to you, knowing that you will do even more than I ask. \n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "b"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "m",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "22",
          "sid": "PHM 1:22"
        },
        "In the meantime, prepare a guest room for me, because I hope that through your prayers I will be restored to you. \n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "s1",
      "content": ["Additional Greetings\n"]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "b"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "m",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "23",
          "sid": "PHM 1:23"
        },
        "Epaphras, my fellow prisoner in Christ Jesus, sends you greetings, \n",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "24",
          "sid": "PHM 1:24"
        },
        "as do Mark, Aristarchus, Demas, and Luke, my fellow workers. \n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "b"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "m",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "25",
          "sid": "PHM 1:25"
        },
        "The grace of the Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit.",
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "f",
          "content": [
            " ",
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": ["1:25 "]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": ["BYZ and TR include Amen."]
            }
          ],
          "caller": "+"
        },
        " "
      ]
    }
  ]
}
